{
  "video_id": "CDsNZJTWw0w",
  "title": "New bionics let us run, climb and dance | Hugh Herr",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13252.0,
      "end_time": 15982.0,
      "text": "Looking deeply inside nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15982.0,
      "end_time": 19095.0,
      "text": "through the magnifying glass of science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19095.0,
      "end_time": 22700.0,
      "text": "designers extract principles, processes and materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22700.0,
      "end_time": 27252.0,
      "text": "that are forming the very basis of design methodology."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27252.0,
      "end_time": 32352.0,
      "text": "From synthetic constructs that resemble biological materials,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32351.999999999996,
      "end_time": 35743.0,
      "text": "to computational methods that emulate neural processes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 35743.0,
      "end_time": 39398.0,
      "text": "nature is driving design."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 39398.0,
      "end_time": 42128.0,
      "text": "Design is also driving nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 42128.0,
      "end_time": 45887.0,
      "text": "In realms of genetics, regenerative medicine and synthetic biology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 45887.0,
      "end_time": 48616.0,
      "text": "designers are growing novel technologies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48616.0,
      "end_time": 53140.0,
      "text": "not foreseen or anticipated by nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 53140.0,
      "end_time": 59107.0,
      "text": "Bionics explores the interplay between biology and design."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 59107.0,
      "end_time": 62990.0,
      "text": "As you can see, my legs are bionic."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 62990.0,
      "end_time": 68538.0,
      "text": "Today, I will tell human stories of bionic integration;"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 68538.0,
      "end_time": 74261.0,
      "text": "how electromechanics attached to the body, and implanted inside the body"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 74261.0,
      "end_time": 78999.0,
      "text": "are beginning to bridge the gap between disability and ability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 78999.0,
      "end_time": 84681.0,
      "text": "between human limitation and human potential."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 84681.0,
      "end_time": 88228.0,
      "text": "Bionics has defined my physicality."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 88228.0,
      "end_time": 90704.0,
      "text": "In 1982, both of my legs were amputated"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 90704.0,
      "end_time": 92832.0,
      "text": "due to tissue damage from frostbite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 92832.0,
      "end_time": 95950.0,
      "text": "incurred during a mountain-climbing accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 95950.0,
      "end_time": 100417.0,
      "text": "At that time, I didn&#39;t view my body as broken."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 100417.0,
      "end_time": 105655.0,
      "text": "I reasoned that a human being can never be &quot;broken.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 105655.0,
      "end_time": 108409.0,
      "text": "Technology is broken."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 108409.0,
      "end_time": 111638.0,
      "text": "Technology is inadequate."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 111638.0,
      "end_time": 116120.0,
      "text": "This simple but powerful idea was a call to arms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 116120.0,
      "end_time": 120651.0,
      "text": "to advance technology for the elimination of my own disability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 120651.0,
      "end_time": 124460.0,
      "text": "and ultimately, the disability of others."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 124460.0,
      "end_time": 127442.0,
      "text": "I began by developing specialized limbs"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 127442.0,
      "end_time": 129927.0,
      "text": "that allowed me to return to the vertical world"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 129926.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131418.0,
      "text": "of rock and ice climbing."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 131418.0,
      "end_time": 136060.0,
      "text": "I quickly realized that the artificial part of my body is malleable;"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 136060.0,
      "end_time": 140434.0,
      "text": "able to take on any form, any function --"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 140434.0,
      "end_time": 143397.0,
      "text": "a blank slate for which to create,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 143397.0,
      "end_time": 149391.0,
      "text": "perhaps, structures that could extend beyond biological capability."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 149391.0,
      "end_time": 150765.0,
      "text": "I made my height adjustable."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 150765.0,
      "end_time": 153469.0,
      "text": "I could be as short as five feet or as tall as I&#39;d like."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 153469.0,
      "end_time": 155922.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 155922.0,
      "end_time": 159296.0,
      "text": "So when I was feeling bad about myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 159296.0,
      "end_time": 161157.0,
      "text": "insecure, I would jack my height up."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 161157.0,
      "end_time": 163062.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 163062.0,
      "end_time": 165283.0,
      "text": "But when I was feeling confident and suave,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 165283.0,
      "end_time": 169076.0,
      "text": "I would knock my height down a notch, just to give the competition a chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 169076.0,
      "end_time": 171195.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 171195.0,
      "end_time": 173322.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 173322.0,
      "end_time": 176615.0,
      "text": "Narrow-edged feet allowed me to climb steep rock fissures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 176615.0,
      "end_time": 179241.0,
      "text": "where the human foot cannot penetrate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 179241.0,
      "end_time": 183447.0,
      "text": "and spiked feet enabled me to climb vertical ice walls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 183447.0,
      "end_time": 187399.0,
      "text": "without ever experiencing muscle leg fatigue."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 187399.0,
      "end_time": 189613.0,
      "text": "Through technological innovation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 189613.0,
      "end_time": 192478.0,
      "text": "I returned to my sport, stronger and better."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 192478.0,
      "end_time": 195085.0,
      "text": "Technology had eliminated my disability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 195085.0,
      "end_time": 197451.0,
      "text": "and allowed me a new climbing prowess."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 197451.0,
      "end_time": 201038.0,
      "text": "As a young man, I imagined a future world where technology so advanced"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 201038.0,
      "end_time": 202844.0,
      "text": "could rid the world of disability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 202844.0,
      "end_time": 204964.0,
      "text": "a world in which neural implants would allow"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 204964.0,
      "end_time": 207026.0,
      "text": "the visually impaired to see."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 207026.0,
      "end_time": 212645.0,
      "text": "A world in which the paralyzed could walk, via body exoskeletons."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 212645.0,
      "end_time": 215447.0,
      "text": "Sadly, because of deficiencies in technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 215447.0,
      "end_time": 217205.0,
      "text": "disability is rampant in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 217205.0,
      "end_time": 219903.0,
      "text": "This gentleman is missing three limbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 219903.0,
      "end_time": 223750.0,
      "text": "As a testimony to current technology, he is out of the wheelchair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 223750.0,
      "end_time": 229695.0,
      "text": "but we need to do a better job in bionics, to allow, one day, full rehabilitation"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 229695.0,
      "end_time": 233876.0,
      "text": "for a person with this level of injury."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 233876.0,
      "end_time": 237479.0,
      "text": "At the MIT Media Lab, we&#39;ve established the Center for Extreme Bionics."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 237479.0,
      "end_time": 242051.0,
      "text": "The mission of the center is to put forth fundamental science"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 242051.0,
      "end_time": 243911.0,
      "text": "and technological capability"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 243911.0,
      "end_time": 247682.0,
      "text": "that will allow the biomechatronic and regenerative repair of humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 247682.0,
      "end_time": 253707.0,
      "text": "across a broad range of brain and body disabilities."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 253707.0,
      "end_time": 257468.0,
      "text": "Today, I&#39;m going to tell you how my legs function, how they work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 257468.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260770.00000000003,
      "text": "as a case in point for this center."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 260769.99999999997,
      "end_time": 262921.0,
      "text": "Now, I made sure to shave my legs last night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 262921.0,
      "end_time": 264892.0,
      "text": "because I knew I&#39;d be showing them off."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 264892.0,
      "end_time": 266365.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 266365.0,
      "end_time": 269619.0,
      "text": "Bionics entails the engineering of extreme interfaces."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 269619.0,
      "end_time": 272515.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s three extreme interfaces in my bionic limbs:"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 272515.0,
      "end_time": 276619.0,
      "text": "mechanical, how my limbs are attached to my biological body;"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 276619.0,
      "end_time": 279942.0,
      "text": "dynamic, how they move like flesh and bone;"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 279942.0,
      "end_time": 282856.0,
      "text": "and electrical, how they communicate with my nervous system."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 282856.0,
      "end_time": 285904.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll begin with mechanical interface."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 285904.0,
      "end_time": 289071.0,
      "text": "In the area of design, we still do not understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 289071.0,
      "end_time": 293185.0,
      "text": "how to attach devices to the body mechanically."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 293185.0,
      "end_time": 296352.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s extraordinary to me that in this day and age,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 296352.0,
      "end_time": 298701.0,
      "text": "one of the most mature, oldest technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 298701.0,
      "end_time": 303121.0,
      "text": "in the human timeline, the shoe, still gives us blisters."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 303121.0,
      "end_time": 304602.0,
      "text": "How can this be?"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 304602.0,
      "end_time": 308364.0,
      "text": "We have no idea how to attach things to our bodies."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 308364.0,
      "end_time": 311293.0,
      "text": "This is the beautifully lyrical design work"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 311293.0,
      "end_time": 313738.0,
      "text": "of Professor Neri Oxman at the MIT Media Lab,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 313738.0,
      "end_time": 317186.0,
      "text": "showing spatially varying exoskeletal impedances,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 317186.0,
      "end_time": 321811.0,
      "text": "shown here by color variation in this 3D-printed model."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 321811.0,
      "end_time": 326359.0,
      "text": "Imagine a future where clothing is stiff and soft where you need it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 326359.0,
      "end_time": 329913.0,
      "text": "when you need it, for optimal support and flexibility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 329913.0,
      "end_time": 332112.0,
      "text": "without ever causing discomfort."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 332112.0,
      "end_time": 335558.0,
      "text": "My bionic limbs are attached to my biological body"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 335558.0,
      "end_time": 339644.0,
      "text": "via synthetic skins with stiffness variations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 339644.0,
      "end_time": 344359.0,
      "text": "that mirror my underlying tissue biomechanics."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 344359.0,
      "end_time": 347557.0,
      "text": "To achieve that mirroring, we first developed a mathematical model"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 347557.0,
      "end_time": 349129.0,
      "text": "of my biological limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 349129.0,
      "end_time": 352435.0,
      "text": "To that end, we used imaging tools such as MRI,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 352435.0,
      "end_time": 354023.0,
      "text": "to look inside my body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 354023.0,
      "end_time": 357752.0,
      "text": "to figure out the geometries and locations of various tissues."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 357752.0,
      "end_time": 359163.0,
      "text": "We also took robotic tools --"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 359163.0,
      "end_time": 364891.0,
      "text": "here&#39;s a 14-actuator circle that goes around the biological limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 364891.0,
      "end_time": 367463.0,
      "text": "The actuators come in, find the surface of the limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 367463.0,
      "end_time": 369732.0,
      "text": "measure its unloaded shape,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 369732.0,
      "end_time": 371407.0,
      "text": "and then they push on the tissues"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 371407.0,
      "end_time": 375542.0,
      "text": "to measure tissue compliances at each anatomical point."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 375542.0,
      "end_time": 377813.0,
      "text": "We combine these imaging and robotic data"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 377813.0,
      "end_time": 381479.0,
      "text": "to build a mathematical description of my biological limb, shown on the left."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 381479.0,
      "end_time": 383257.0,
      "text": "You see a bunch of points, or nodes?"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 383257.0,
      "end_time": 386431.0,
      "text": "At each node, there&#39;s a color that represents tissue compliance."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 386431.0,
      "end_time": 390397.0,
      "text": "We then do a mathematical transformation to the design of the synthetic skin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 390397.0,
      "end_time": 392088.0,
      "text": "shown on the right."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 392088.0,
      "end_time": 394516.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ve discovered optimality is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 394516.0,
      "end_time": 397397.0,
      "text": "where the body is stiff, the synthetic skin should be soft,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 397397.0,
      "end_time": 400881.0,
      "text": "where the body is soft, the synthetic skin is stiff,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 400881.0,
      "end_time": 404720.0,
      "text": "and this mirroring occurs across all tissue compliances."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 404720.0,
      "end_time": 407505.0,
      "text": "With this framework, we&#39;ve produced bionic limbs"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 407505.0,
      "end_time": 411077.0,
      "text": "that are the most comfortable limbs I&#39;ve ever worn."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 411077.0,
      "end_time": 417190.0,
      "text": "Clearly, in the future, our clothing, our shoes, our braces, our prostheses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 417190.0,
      "end_time": 420870.0,
      "text": "will no longer be designed and manufactured using artisan strategies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 420870.0,
      "end_time": 424098.0,
      "text": "but rather, data-driven quantitative frameworks."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 424098.0,
      "end_time": 429040.0,
      "text": "In that future, our shoes will no longer give us blisters."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 429040.0,
      "end_time": 431961.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re also embedding sensing and smart materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 431961.0,
      "end_time": 433556.0,
      "text": "into the synthetic skins."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 433556.0,
      "end_time": 438048.0,
      "text": "This is a material developed by SRI International, California."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 438048.0,
      "end_time": 441349.0,
      "text": "Under electrostatic effect, it changes stiffness."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 441349.0,
      "end_time": 444698.0,
      "text": "So under zero voltage, the material is compliant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 444698.0,
      "end_time": 446096.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s floppy like paper."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 446096.0,
      "end_time": 448588.0,
      "text": "Then the button&#39;s pushed, a voltage is applied,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 448588.0,
      "end_time": 450604.0,
      "text": "and it becomes stiff as a board."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 450604.0,
      "end_time": 453666.0,
      "text": "(Tapping sounds)"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 453666.0,
      "end_time": 456338.0,
      "text": "We embed this material into the synthetic skin"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 456338.0,
      "end_time": 459888.0,
      "text": "that attaches my bionic limb to my biological body."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 459888.0,
      "end_time": 462342.0,
      "text": "When I walk here, it&#39;s no voltage."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 462342.0,
      "end_time": 464423.0,
      "text": "My interface is soft and compliant."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 464423.0,
      "end_time": 467438.0,
      "text": "The button&#39;s pushed, voltage is applied, and it stiffens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 467438.0,
      "end_time": 470915.0,
      "text": "offering me a greater maneuverability over the bionic limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 470915.0,
      "end_time": 473327.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re also building exoskeletons."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 473327.0,
      "end_time": 475607.0,
      "text": "This exoskeleton becomes stiff and soft"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 475607.0,
      "end_time": 478569.0,
      "text": "in just the right areas of the running cycle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 478569.0,
      "end_time": 482847.0,
      "text": "to protect the biological joints from high impacts and degradation."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 482847.0,
      "end_time": 485657.0,
      "text": "In the future, we&#39;ll all be wearing exoskeletons"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 485657.0,
      "end_time": 488966.0,
      "text": "in common activities, such as running."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 488966.0,
      "end_time": 490474.0,
      "text": "Next, dynamic interface."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 490474.0,
      "end_time": 493799.0,
      "text": "How do my bionic limbs move like flesh and bone?"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 493799.0,
      "end_time": 497808.0,
      "text": "At my MIT lab, we study how humans with normal physiologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 497808.0,
      "end_time": 499338.0,
      "text": "stand, walk and run."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 499338.0,
      "end_time": 500753.0,
      "text": "What are the muscles doing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 500753.0,
      "end_time": 503697.0,
      "text": "and how are they controlled by the spinal cord?"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 503697.0,
      "end_time": 506166.0,
      "text": "This basic science motivates what we build."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 506166.0,
      "end_time": 508528.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re building bionic ankles, knees and hips."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 508528.0,
      "end_time": 511854.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re building body parts from the ground up."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 511854.0,
      "end_time": 515041.0,
      "text": "The bionic limbs that I&#39;m wearing are called BiOMs."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 515041.00000000006,
      "end_time": 519019.00000000006,
      "text": "They&#39;ve been fitted to nearly 1,000 patients,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 519019.0,
      "end_time": 522005.0,
      "text": "400 of which have been wounded U.S. soldiers."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 522005.0,
      "end_time": 523187.0,
      "text": "How does it work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 523187.0,
      "end_time": 525226.0,
      "text": "At heel strike, under computer control,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 525226.0,
      "end_time": 527226.0,
      "text": "the system controls stiffness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 527226.0,
      "end_time": 530287.0,
      "text": "to attenuate the shock of the limb hitting the ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 530287.0,
      "end_time": 534407.0,
      "text": "Then at mid-stance, the bionic limb outputs high torques and powers"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 534407.0,
      "end_time": 536786.0,
      "text": "to lift the person into the walking stride,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 536786.0,
      "end_time": 541096.0,
      "text": "comparable to how muscles work in the calf region."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 541096.0,
      "end_time": 544850.0,
      "text": "This bionic propulsion is very important clinically to patients."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 544850.0,
      "end_time": 547928.0,
      "text": "So on the left, you see the bionic device worn by a lady,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 547928.0,
      "end_time": 550887.0,
      "text": "on the right, a passive device worn by the same lady,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 550887.0,
      "end_time": 553737.0,
      "text": "that fails to emulate normal muscle function,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 553737.0,
      "end_time": 557439.0,
      "text": "enabling her to do something everyone should be able to do:"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 557439.0,
      "end_time": 559634.0,
      "text": "go up and down their steps at home."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 559634.0,
      "end_time": 563149.0,
      "text": "Bionics also allows for extraordinary athletic feats."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 563149.0,
      "end_time": 567784.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s a gentleman running up a rocky pathway."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 567784.0,
      "end_time": 570633.0,
      "text": "This is Steve Martin -- not the comedian --"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 570633.0,
      "end_time": 574327.0,
      "text": "who lost his legs in a bomb blast in Afghanistan."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 574327.0,
      "end_time": 579218.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re also building exoskeletal structures using these same principles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 579218.0,
      "end_time": 582311.0,
      "text": "that wrap around the biological limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 582311.0,
      "end_time": 587922.0,
      "text": "This gentleman does not have any leg condition, any disability."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 587922.0,
      "end_time": 589826.0,
      "text": "He has a normal physiology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 589826.0,
      "end_time": 594419.0,
      "text": "so these exoskeletons are applying muscle-like torques and powers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 594419.0,
      "end_time": 599079.0,
      "text": "so that his own muscles need not apply those torques and powers."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 599079.0,
      "end_time": 604501.0,
      "text": "This is the first exoskeleton in history that actually augments human walking."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 604501.0,
      "end_time": 607668.0,
      "text": "It significantly reduces metabolic cost."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 607668.0,
      "end_time": 610406.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s so profound in its augmentation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 610406.0,
      "end_time": 613579.0,
      "text": "that when a normal, healthy person wears the device for 40 minutes"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 613579.0,
      "end_time": 615302.0,
      "text": "and then takes it off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 615302.0,
      "end_time": 620039.0,
      "text": "their own biological legs feel ridiculously heavy and awkward."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 620039.0,
      "end_time": 623474.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re beginning the age in which machines attached to our bodies"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 623474.0,
      "end_time": 627699.0,
      "text": "will make us stronger and faster and more efficient."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 627699.0,
      "end_time": 629470.0,
      "text": "Moving on to electrical interface:"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 629470.0,
      "end_time": 632651.0,
      "text": "How do my bionic limbs communicate with my nervous system?"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 632651.0,
      "end_time": 634517.0,
      "text": "Across my residual limb are electrodes"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 634517.0,
      "end_time": 637286.0,
      "text": "that measure the electrical pulse of my muscles."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 637286.0,
      "end_time": 639229.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s communicated to the bionic limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 639229.0,
      "end_time": 642306.0,
      "text": "so when I think about moving my phantom limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 642306.0,
      "end_time": 646020.0,
      "text": "the robot tracks those movement desires."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 646020.0,
      "end_time": 650670.0,
      "text": "This diagram shows fundamentally how the bionic limb is controlled."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 650670.0,
      "end_time": 653099.0,
      "text": "So we model the missing biological limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 653099.0,
      "end_time": 655937.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;ve discovered what reflexes occurred,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 655937.0,
      "end_time": 659302.0,
      "text": "how the reflexes of the spinal cord are controlling the muscles."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 659302.0,
      "end_time": 665009.0,
      "text": "And that capability is embedded in the chips of the bionic limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 665009.0,
      "end_time": 668993.0,
      "text": "What we&#39;ve done, then, is we modulate the sensitivity of the reflex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 668993.0,
      "end_time": 672112.0,
      "text": "the modeled spinal reflex, with the neural signal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 672112.0,
      "end_time": 675565.0,
      "text": "so when I relax my muscles in my residual limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 675565.0,
      "end_time": 678436.0,
      "text": "I get very little torque and power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 678436.0,
      "end_time": 681181.0,
      "text": "but the more I fire my muscles, the more torque I get,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 681181.0,
      "end_time": 684014.0,
      "text": "and I can even run."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 684014.0,
      "end_time": 688982.0,
      "text": "And that was the first demonstration of a running gait under neural command."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 688982.0,
      "end_time": 690158.0,
      "text": "Feels great."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 690158.0,
      "end_time": 696149.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 696149.0,
      "end_time": 697558.0,
      "text": "We want to go a step further."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 697558.0,
      "end_time": 700629.0,
      "text": "We want to actually close the loop"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 700629.0,
      "end_time": 704407.0,
      "text": "between the human and the bionic external limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 704407.0,
      "end_time": 705582.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re doing experiments"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 705582.0,
      "end_time": 708075.0,
      "text": "where we&#39;re growing nerves, transected nerves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 708075.0,
      "end_time": 710129.0,
      "text": "through channels, or micro-channel arrays."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 710129.0,
      "end_time": 711847.0,
      "text": "On the other side of the channel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 711847.0,
      "end_time": 714200.0,
      "text": "the nerve then attaches to cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 714200.0,
      "end_time": 716926.0,
      "text": "skin cells and muscle cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 716926.0,
      "end_time": 721070.0,
      "text": "In the motor channels, we can sense how the person wishes to move."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 721070.0,
      "end_time": 724731.0,
      "text": "That can be sent out wirelessly to the bionic limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 724731.0,
      "end_time": 727137.0,
      "text": "then [sensory information] on the bionic limb"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 727137.0,
      "end_time": 730662.0,
      "text": "can be converted to stimulations in adjacent channels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 730662.0,
      "end_time": 731918.0,
      "text": "sensory channels."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 731918.0,
      "end_time": 735970.0,
      "text": "So when this is fully developed and for human use,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 735970.0,
      "end_time": 738630.0,
      "text": "persons like myself will not only have"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 738630.0,
      "end_time": 742187.0,
      "text": "synthetic limbs that move like flesh and bone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 742187.0,
      "end_time": 746187.0,
      "text": "but actually feel like flesh and bone."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 746187.0,
      "end_time": 748201.0,
      "text": "This video shows Lisa Mallette,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 748201.0,
      "end_time": 751471.0,
      "text": "shortly after being fitted with two bionic limbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 751471.0,
      "end_time": 754988.0,
      "text": "Indeed, bionics is making a profound difference in people&#39;s lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 754988.0,
      "end_time": 759519.0,
      "text": "(Video) Lisa Mallette: Oh my God."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 759519.0,
      "end_time": 762678.0,
      "text": "LM: Oh my God, I can&#39;t believe it!"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 762678.0,
      "end_time": 764145.0,
      "text": "(Video) (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 764145.0,
      "end_time": 769237.0,
      "text": "LM: It&#39;s just like I&#39;ve got a real leg!"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 769237.0,
      "end_time": 770855.0,
      "text": "Woman: Now, don&#39;t start running."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 770855.0,
      "end_time": 773673.0,
      "text": "Man: Now turn around, and do the same thing walking up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 773673.0,
      "end_time": 777426.0,
      "text": "but get on your heel to toe, like you would normally just walk on level ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 777426.0,
      "end_time": 781411.0,
      "text": "Try to walk right up the hill."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 781411.0,
      "end_time": 784037.0,
      "text": "LM: Oh my God."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 784037.0,
      "end_time": 785307.0,
      "text": "Man: Is it pushing you up?"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 785307.0,
      "end_time": 790286.0,
      "text": "LM: Yes! I&#39;m not even -- I can&#39;t even describe it."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 790286.0,
      "end_time": 792608.0,
      "text": "Man: It&#39;s pushing you right up."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 792608.0,
      "end_time": 795180.0,
      "text": "Hugh Herr: Next week, I&#39;m visiting the Center --"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 795180.0,
      "end_time": 796356.0,
      "text": "Thank you. Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 796356.0,
      "end_time": 799886.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 799886.0,
      "end_time": 801193.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 801193.0,
      "end_time": 805042.0,
      "text": "Next week I&#39;m visiting the Center for Medicare and Medicaid Services,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 805042.0,
      "end_time": 807669.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m going to try to convince CMS"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 807669.0,
      "end_time": 810248.0,
      "text": "to grant appropriate code language and pricing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 810248.0,
      "end_time": 814003.0,
      "text": "so this technology can be made available to the patients that need it."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 814003.0,
      "end_time": 815050.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 815050.0,
      "end_time": 816234.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 816234.0,
      "end_time": 819873.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 819873.0,
      "end_time": 823841.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not well appreciated, but over half of the world&#39;s population"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 823841.0,
      "end_time": 828632.0,
      "text": "suffers from some form of cognitive, emotional, sensory or motor condition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 828632.0,
      "end_time": 833066.0,
      "text": "and because of poor technology, too often, conditions result in disability"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 833066.0,
      "end_time": 835113.0,
      "text": "and a poorer quality of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 835113.0,
      "end_time": 840077.0,
      "text": "Basic levels of physiological function should be a part of our human rights."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 840077.0,
      "end_time": 844057.0,
      "text": "Every person should have the right to live life without disability"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 844057.0,
      "end_time": 845978.0,
      "text": "if they so choose --"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 845978.0,
      "end_time": 848724.0,
      "text": "the right to live life without severe depression;"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 848724.0,
      "end_time": 852129.0,
      "text": "the right to see a loved one, in the case of seeing-impaired;"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 852129.0,
      "end_time": 854042.0,
      "text": "or the right to walk or to dance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 854042.0,
      "end_time": 857633.0,
      "text": "in the case of limb paralysis or limb amputation."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 857633.0,
      "end_time": 861323.0,
      "text": "As a society, we can achieve these human rights,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 861323.0,
      "end_time": 867794.0,
      "text": "if we accept the proposition that humans are not disabled."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 867794.0,
      "end_time": 870500.0,
      "text": "A person can never be broken."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 870500.0,
      "end_time": 873199.0,
      "text": "Our built environment, our technologies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 873199.0,
      "end_time": 875444.0,
      "text": "are broken and disabled."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 875444.0,
      "end_time": 878500.0,
      "text": "We the people need not accept our limitations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 878500.0,
      "end_time": 882599.0,
      "text": "but can transcend disability through technological innovation."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 882599.0,
      "end_time": 886583.0,
      "text": "Indeed, through fundamental advances in bionics in this century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 886583.0,
      "end_time": 890765.0,
      "text": "we will set the technological foundation for an enhanced human experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 890765.0,
      "end_time": 893456.0,
      "text": "and we will end disability."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 893456.0,
      "end_time": 897613.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to finish up with one more story, a beautiful story."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 897613.0,
      "end_time": 900360.0,
      "text": "The story of Adrianne Haslet-Davis."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 900360.0,
      "end_time": 904766.0,
      "text": "Adrianne lost her left leg in the Boston terrorist attack."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 904766.0,
      "end_time": 908745.0,
      "text": "I met Adrianne when this photo was taken, at Spaulding Rehabilitation Hospital."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 908745.0,
      "end_time": 911245.0,
      "text": "Adrianne is a dancer, a ballroom dancer."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 911245.0,
      "end_time": 914366.0,
      "text": "Adrianne breathes and lives dance."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 914366.0,
      "end_time": 916660.0,
      "text": "It is her expression. It is her art form."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 916660.0,
      "end_time": 920683.0,
      "text": "Naturally, when she lost her limb in the Boston terrorist attack,"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 920683.0,
      "end_time": 923828.0,
      "text": "she wanted to return to the dance floor."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 923828.0,
      "end_time": 926011.0,
      "text": "After meeting her and driving home in my car,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 926011.0,
      "end_time": 929888.0,
      "text": "I thought, I&#39;m an MIT professor. I have resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 929888.0,
      "end_time": 931450.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s build her a bionic limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 931450.0,
      "end_time": 935396.0,
      "text": "to enable her to go back to her life of dance."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 935396.0,
      "end_time": 938896.0,
      "text": "I brought in MIT scientists with expertise in prosthetics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 938896.0,
      "end_time": 941229.0,
      "text": "robotics, machine learning and biomechanics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 941229.0,
      "end_time": 945389.0,
      "text": "and over a 200-day research period, we studied dance."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 945389.0,
      "end_time": 949310.0,
      "text": "We brought in dancers with biological limbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 949310.0,
      "end_time": 951969.0,
      "text": "and we studied how they move,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 951969.0,
      "end_time": 955166.0,
      "text": "what forces they apply on the dance floor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 955166.0,
      "end_time": 956717.0,
      "text": "and we took those data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 956717.0,
      "end_time": 960516.0,
      "text": "and we put forth fundamental principles of dance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 960516.0,
      "end_time": 962327.0,
      "text": "reflexive dance capability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 962327.0,
      "end_time": 965992.0,
      "text": "and we embedded that intelligence into the bionic limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 965992.0,
      "end_time": 969761.0,
      "text": "Bionics is not only about making people stronger and faster."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 969761.0,
      "end_time": 975520.0,
      "text": "Our expression, our humanity can be embedded into electromechanics."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 975520.0,
      "end_time": 981733.0,
      "text": "It was 3.5 seconds between the bomb blasts in the Boston terrorist attack."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 981733.0,
      "end_time": 987860.0,
      "text": "In 3.5 seconds, the criminals and cowards took Adrianne off the dance floor."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 987860.0,
      "end_time": 990495.0,
      "text": "In 200 days, we put her back."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 990495.0,
      "end_time": 995492.0,
      "text": "We will not be intimidated, brought down, diminished, conquered or stopped"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 995492.0,
      "end_time": 997061.0,
      "text": "by acts of violence."
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 997061.0,
      "end_time": 1005046.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 1005050.0,
      "end_time": 1009376.0,
      "text": "Ladies and gentlemen, please allow me to introduce Adrianne Haslet-Davis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 1009370.0,
      "end_time": 1012378.0,
      "text": "her first performance since the attack."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 1012380.0,
      "end_time": 1014541.0,
      "text": "She&#39;s dancing with Christian Lightner."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 1014540.0,
      "end_time": 1025578.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 1025579.9999999999,
      "end_time": 1071268.0,
      "text": "(Music: &quot;Ring My Bell&quot; performed by Enrique Iglesias)"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 1071270.0,
      "end_time": 1102173.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 1102170.0,
      "end_time": 1104962.0,
      "text": "Ladies and gentlemen, members of the research team:"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 1104960.0,
      "end_time": 1106979.0,
      "text": "Elliott Rouse"
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 1106980.0,
      "end_time": 1109775.0,
      "text": "and Nathan Villagaray-Carski."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 1109780.0,
      "end_time": 1112191.0,
      "text": "Elliott and Nathan."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 1112190.0,
      "end_time": 1122190.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}